      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The consensus among modern historians is that the UN has been an inconsistent and often deeply flawed mechanism for preventing major conflicts in the 21st century. While it has achieved some localized successes through peacekeeping missions, its effectiveness is consistently undermined by the veto power wielded by permanent Security Council members. Ultimately, the UN's inability to enforce its own resolutions when great power interests clash proves its structural limitations in stopping large-scale wars.",
