      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The criticism is rarely about the UN being \"broken\"; it's almost always a critique of the flawed geopolitical reality it is forced to navigate. Most serious analysts view the UN as a necessary, yet inherently compromised, forum for international dialogue. The institution functions as a reflection of the current balance of power, meaning its failures are less a design flaw and more a predictable outcome of great power self-interest.",
      "source": "target",
