    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so it's basically seen as a tool that only works when the big powers agree? if that's the case, does that mean the whole idea of \"international law\" or the UN's authority is actually just a useful fiction, or is there a legitimate argument that it still holds real weight even when countries ignore it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
