      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "International law, when enforced by the UN, is often a useful fiction that serves the interests of powerful nations. However, even when ignored, the framework of international law still holds significant practical weight because it establishes norms and creates diplomatic costs for violators. Nations still operate within a shared system of expectations, and blatant disregard for these rules invites international condemnation and economic pressure.",
      "source": "target",
